main event: Multiple witnesses reported an explosion in wild mountainous country near Rodeo, New Mexico, with a piece of metal resembling a 'rear head' for a guided missile found at the site.
interesting points: Mr. Campbell, a patrolman of the Border Patrol, reported an explosion and discovered a swath in the brush and timber culminating in a huge crater.
A piece of metal about 12 inches in diameter and pointed, believed to be a 'rear head' for a guided missile, was found at the explosion site.
The explosion was originally thought to be a crashed plane, but nothing resembling a plane was found at the site.
The site of the explosion was in wild mountainous country, about ten miles east of Rodeo, New Mexico, with the nearest landing field by plane being at Rodeo.
The preliminary investigation revealed the explosion to have been caused by the detonation of a practice type bomb used by the United States Air Force.
location: wild mountainous country near Rodeo, New Mexico
